A van with two thousand kilos of hashish passes the checkpoint in Alava
Five minus ten in the morning.
The agents order the alt to the two occupants of a van who instead of stopping flee.
The agents ordered the alt to the two occupants of a van who instead of stopping fled to escape.
Their load, more than two tons of hashish, is a good reason not to stop.
The agents after chasing them, manage to arrest one of the two occupants, a man of about 28 years, identified as A. A. J., according to a statement from the Department of the Interior of the Basque government.
The arrested individual is charged with drug trafficking and falsifying public documents.
The accident occurred when officials of the Alava road were carrying out a transport check on the N-1, at the point where it crosses the municipal district of Armiñón.
They were about to stop a van for inspection when the driver, breaking orders, accelerated sharply and crossed the checkpoint.
The officers gave chase until the vehicle, after a couple of kilometers, stopped on the side of the road and its two occupants fled into a wooded area.
The Ertzaintza agents then managed to arrest one of the fugitives and seize the 2,178 kilograms of hashish they were transporting and took note of it once the van, an Iveco Daily, was inspected.
