Ertzaintza is continuing its investigation to arrest the second suspect, who managed to escape as already mentioned, and to determine the origin of the seized drugs.
Detainee A. A. J., 28, was taken to the police station to carry out the appropriate procedures and be available to the judge in the coming hours.
Actress Heather Locklear arrested for driving under the influence of drugs
Actress Heather Locklear, the Amanda of the popular series Melrose Place, was arrested this weekend in Santa Barbara, California, for driving under the influence of drugs.
A witness saw her perform risky maneuvers while trying to get out of the parking lot in Montecito, a spokesperson for the Californian road car told People magazine.
The witness specified that around 4.30 pm Locklear "pressed the accelerator thoroughly, making a lot of noise, and trying to get the car out of the parking lot with abrupt maneuvers back and forth. Reversing, he passed his sunglasses several times."
Shortly after, the witness, who at first glance, apparently did not recognize the actress, saw that Locklear had stopped in a nearby street and exited the vehicle.
It was this person who alerted the emergency services, because "she was worried about Locklear's life."
When the police patrol arrived, they found the actress sitting inside her vehicle, partially blocking the road.
"She looked confused," so officers took her to a specialist drug and alcohol treatment center for testing.
According to a police spokesperson, the actress was cooperative and the hypothesis of excess alcohol was discarded from the beginning, although "according to what the officers observed at first, we believe that Locklear was under the influence of some drug."
Locklear was arrested on suspicion of driving under the influence of some unspecified substance and was locked up in the local prison around 7 p.m., to be released a few hours later.
Two months ago, Locklear recovered from a specialty clinic in Arizona after being admitted following an episode of anxiety and depression.
Llamazares urges Andalusian UI federation to assume its responsibilities in Silva case
The general coordinator of the UI and member of the Izquierda Unida party, Gaspar Llamazares, confirmed today that it will be up to the regional federation of training to make a decision on the case of the former councilor for Youth and Sports of the City of Seville, Francisco Manuel Silva, who resigned last week following accusations of cronyism.
